==English==

===Etymology===
From the verb '''to [[rock]]''' + ''[[-er]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[curved]] piece of wood attached to the bottom of a [[rocking chair]] or [[cradle]] that enables it to [[rock]] back and forth.
# Hence, a [[rocking chair]]
# {{surfing}} The lengthwise [[curvature]] of a [[surfboard]].  (More rocker is a more curved board.)
#: ''All modern surfboards share a similar rocker design'' &mdash; Bruce Jones [http://www.brucejones.com/longboar.htm]
# Someone passionate about [[rock music]].
# One who [[rock]]s something.

